<b>Dragon pulling - </b>11/9/01 4:26:36 PM<br>~ <b>Arud Bastad</b><blockquote>Since most high level dragons like Gore, Talendor etc see thru invis, I like to use this song to pull those dragons so I dont agro other mobs in a heavily populated zone. I always keep Selos memmed just in case though.<br></blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Tricks to group travel - </b>8/13/01 5:12:24 PM<br>~ <b>Arolpin Lorespinner</b><blockquote>The secret to traveling with this song is to have everyone follow one person OTHER than the bard.  I will always call who is leader, tell everyone to auto-follow that person, then explain that if they are following me, there is a very good chance that they will fall back and fall to their death.  Nothing like a bit of fear to get them to pay attention.  <br>Tell the leader to not go until he gets the signal from you and don't give the signal until you see everyone levitating and invisable.  Invariably someone hasn't taken off SoW.  Once you give the leader the signal to start, switch to 3rd person view behind and to one side, and zoom out so that you can see the entire group.  Monitor status and tell the leader to stop if you see anyone fall behind.<br>If you have one person who seems to alwasy fall victim to lag, make him lead.  You'll still end up waiting for him, but you don't have to find him also.<br><br>Arolpin Lorespinner<br>Bard of the 55th Song</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Amazing Range - </b>5/3/01 5:21:33 PM<br>~ <b>Belark Songstrider</b><blockquote>Note that this song will not take hold on any members of your party with SoW or wolf form.<br><br>Think of this song as outdoor group invisibility song with the bonus of levitation, see invisible, and extra speed. Until you get used to this concept, it's easy to get in trouble with this song.<br><br>If you are attacked in any way, the song will wear off like invisibility normally would. Unfortunately, you also lose the speed, see invisible, and levitation when this happens. This applies to your group too, so they need to be aware of it and call for help if attacked, or you will leave them in the dust. They will have no clue where you went.<br><br>I'd recommend that you always have Selo's Accelerando up when using this song, just in case someone is attacked. <br><br>The best thing about this song is the range: very high.. I would estimate it at almost almost 300M, at least double any other bard song I know of.  This alone makes the song worth using.<br><br>A few tips for traveling with this song: Have your members use auto follow, and tell them to stay close to the ground. If attacked while high in the sky, they will plummet down to earth. If they go out of range, they will also plummet. Also make sure they have a &quot;STOP!!&quot; button hot keyed if they lose you. If this happens, they won't see you and might begin running in random directions. Tell them to sit still until you can track to them, and all should be well.<br><br>-Belark Songstrider, 51st Minstrel of Drinal<br></blockquote></td></tr></table></blockquote><br><br><br><br><br><br><a href="/songs.asp?&song=59">Back to Normal Mode</a><br><br><br><i>Printed from EQDiva.com on 2/20/02 1:08:51 PM.</i><br><br></td></tr></table>
